German Mining Museum looks at central issues from German-German environmental history, focusing on the mining carried out between 1949 and 1990, and the use of land leftover from mining. It addresses three different mining categories and regions: lignite mining in Lausitz, coal mining in the Ruhr region, and the uranium ore mining carried out by SDAG Wismut in Thüringia and Saxony.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aBergbaugeschichte. 4aDDR. 4aRekultivierung. 4aUmwelt. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aEnvironment.  aGDR.  aMining history.  aRecultivation.1 aAhlers, Nadine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumert, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDempewolf, Carsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiercks, Thorsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrenkopf, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarrenkopf, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGanzelewski, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGöschl, Regina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGöschl, Regina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMeyer, Torsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMöllers, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrzigoda, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPyhel, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoetbeer, Cornelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrischler, Helmuth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/rela